strategy: Compute store-item revenue and store average in one pass using window functions. Pre-filter date_dim, store, and item using CTEs, then join once via lateral join that pushes filters. Replace division
what_worked: Applied decorrelate, date_cte_isolate, multi_dimension_prefetch: 1) Materialized filtered dimension tables (dates, store, item) into CTEs 2) Consolidated two identical fact table scans into a single CTE that computes per-item revenue and per-store average using window functions 3) Replaced division with multiplication and pushed revenue threshold filter into main WHERE clause.
why_it_worked: Correlated subqueries re-execute per outer row; converting to JOIN eliminates per-row overhead; Pre-filtering date dimension into CTE reduces hash join probe table from 73K to ~365 rows; Pre-filtering multiple dimension tables in parallel reduces join fan-out
